LAGOS  – Sequel to his earlier promise to deliver more housing units to Lagosians, the Lagos State Commissioner for Housing Honourable Moruf Akinderu-Fatai has reaffirmed his ministry’s commitment to actualise this goal before the end of the second quarter of 2022. According to him, the ministry is working assiduously in making sure that this dream comes to fruition His words: “We have the mandate of Mr. Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu to deliver more houses to Lagosians in line with his THEMES agenda of his administration. Urban Development Policy Underway – LASG We Are Using Advocacy To Stamp Out Quackery In Our Profession –… According to him, Mr. Governor since his inauguration as the Governor of the state, has taken the issue of the provision of affordable housing for Lagosians as one of his key developmental project’s hence,the construction and commissioning of several housing units in the five divisions of the state. The Commissioner noted, that in the last two and half years, the state government has built and commissioned different housing units in Ibeshe,Sangotedo,Ajah,Ikorodu, to mention just to mentoo a few. He pointed out, that last year was full of activities for the ministry in terms of the number of houses built and commissioned by the Governor, adding that this year would see more housing units being delivered to Lagosians of different cadre.  